  "text": "Grafana implements a comprehensive three-tier permission model (Viewer/Editor/Admin) across its codebase. The model is defined and enforced through the following key components:\n\n## Role Definition\nThe three-tier role hierarchy is defined in `pkg/apimachinery/identity/role_type.go` as RoleType constants (RoleViewer, RoleEditor, RoleAdmin). These roles are imported and used in `pkg/services/org/model.go` to define organization-level roles. The role_type.go file includes a precedence system where Admin > Editor > Viewer, with the Includes() and Children()/Parents() methods supporting role inheritance semantics.\n\n## Role-to-Permission Mapping\nThe `pkg/services/accesscontrol/roles.go` file contains BuildBasicRoleDefinitions() which maps the three org roles to RoleDTO structures with empty permissions initially. The actual permissions are added through the fixed role registration system in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/dashboard.go` and `pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/folder.go`. \n\nIn ossaccesscontrol/dashboard.go, the roles are mapped as follows:\n- DashboardViewActions: ActionDashboardsRead\n- DashboardEditActions: Extends view with ActionDashboardsWrite, ActionDashboardsDelete\n- DashboardAdminActions: Extends edit with ActionDashboardsPermissionsRead, ActionDashboardsPermissionsWrite\n\nSimilarly in ossaccesscontrol/folder.go:\n- FolderViewActions: ActionFoldersRead, ActionAlertingRuleRead, etc.\n- FolderEditActions: Extends view with ActionFoldersWrite, ActionFoldersDelete, ActionDashboardsCreate\n- FolderAdminActions: Extends edit with ActionFoldersPermissionsRead, ActionFoldersPermissionsWrite\n\nThe registerDashboardRoles() and registerFolderRoles() functions register these roles with Grants to the organization roles [\"Viewer\"], [\"Editor\"], and [\"Admin\"] respectively.\n\n## Permission Guard Middleware\nThe `pkg/services/accesscontrol/middleware.go` file implements the core permission enforcement through the Middleware() function. This middleware intercepts requests and calls authorize() which evaluates user permissions against required permissions using an Evaluator. The AuthorizeInOrgMiddleware() extends this to handle cross-organization authorization scenarios.\n\nThe authorization flow uses `pkg/services/accesscontrol/evaluator.go` which implements the Evaluator interface for permission evaluation, and `pkg/services/accesscontrol/checker.go` which provides the Checker function to verify if a user has specific actions and scopes.\n\nThe `pkg/services/accesscontrol/accesscontrol.go` file provides GetOrgRoles() to extract the org role from the user identity and ReqHasRole() as a fallback authorization mechanism.\n\n## Folder and Dashboard Permission Inheritance\nThe `pkg/services/dashboards/accesscontrol.go` file implements scope resolution for folder and dashboard hierarchies through GetInheritedScopes(). This function retrieves parent folders using folderSvc.GetParents() and builds a list of inherited scopes that apply to child resources.\n\nNewFolderUIDScopeResolver() and NewDashboardUIDScopeResolver() use GetInheritedScopes() to resolve permission scopes, ensuring that permissions are inherited from parent folders. The resolveDashboardScope() function builds the complete scope chain including the dashboard's folder and all ancestor folders.\n\nThe `pkg/services/folder/model.go` defines the Folder structure with ParentUID field for establishing the folder hierarchy. The `pkg/services/folder/service.go` provides the GetParents() method to retrieve the complete parent chain.\n\nThe `pkg/services/dashboards/dashboardaccess/dashboard_access.go` defines the permission types (PERMISSION_VIEW, PERMISSION_EDIT, PERMISSION_ADMIN) for dashboards and folders, which map to the three-tier model.\n\nThe `pkg/api/accesscontrol.go` file declares fixed roles in the HTTPServer.declareFixedRoles() method, registering Viewer/Editor/Admin roles with their respective permissions and grants, completing the permission model implementation."
